quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,31,"Abraham said, “Then what is your mission, O messengers?”",""
  51,32,"They said, “We have been sent to a wicked people,",""
  51,33,"to send down upon them stones of clay,",""
  51,34,"marked by your Lord for the transgressors.”",""
  51,35,"We brought out those believers who were there,",""
  51,36,"but We only found in it one Muslim household<sup>8</sup>.","[8] Lot's family except his wife."
  51,37,"And We left there a sign<sup>9</sup> for those who fear the painful punishment.","[9] i.e., the ruins of Sodom or the Dead Sea in Palestine, as a lesson for people."
  51,38,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Moses when We sent him to Pharaoh with compelling proofs,",""
  51,39,"But he and his supporters turned away, and he said about [Moses], “A magician or a madman!”",""
  51,40,"So We seized him and his soldiers and cast them into the sea while he was blameworthy<sup>10</sup>.","[10] For his disbelief and arrogance."
  51,41,"And [there is a sign in the story of] ‘Ād, when We sent against them the devastating barren wind<sup>11</sup>.","[11] Devoid of all goodness such as carrying rain or fertilizing trees."
  51,42,"It spared nothing it came upon except that it reduced it to ruin and decay.",""
  51,43,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Thamūd, when they were told, “Enjoy yourselves for a while<sup>12</sup>.”","[12] i.e., only three days. See 11:65."
  51,44,"But they rebelled against the command of their Lord, so the thunderbolt seized them, while they were looking on.",""
  51,45,"They could not withstand it, nor could they ward it off.",""
  51,46,"And the people of Noah [were also destroyed] before them. They were indeed a rebellious people.",""
  51,47,"We built the heaven with might<sup>13</sup>, and We are indeed expanding it.","[13] ’Ayd does not mean ""hands"" here. This is not from the verses of Allah's attributes, for Allah Almighty did not add it to Himself, i.e., He did not say, ""My ’ayd, or Our ’ayd""."
  51,48,"And We spread out the earth. How well did We smooth it out<sup>14</sup>!","[14] The earth was spread out to accommodate the creatures. Its spherical shape is mentioned in 39:5."
  51,49,"And We have created everything in pairs<sup>15</sup>, so that you may take heed.","[15] Such as day and night, male and female, light and darkness, sweet and bitter, hot and cold, etc."
  51,50,"So flee to Allah<sup>16</sup>. Indeed, I am a clear warner to you from Him.","[16] From His punishment to His reward by shunning disbelief and sin and by obeying Him."
  51,51,"And do not set up another god with Allah. Indeed, I am a clear warner to you from Him.”",""
